=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
We need to propose a synthetic route from anisole with para-methyl? Wait starting material: COc1ccc(C)cc1 is anisole (methoxy) with para methyl? Actually anisole is methoxy phenyl; the SMILES: COc1ccc(C)cc1: methoxy at position 1, methyl at para (4). So 4-methylanisole (p-tol anisole). Target: COc1ccc(C(=O)N(C)C)cc1: same anisole ring with para-acetamide dimethyl? Actually carbonyl attached to aromatic: para-acetamide with N,N-dimethyl? Wait C(=O)N(C)C is dimethylcarbamoyl group attached to aromatic carbon (para). So we need to convert para-methyl group to para-acetamide (dimethyl). So transformation: oxidation of methyl to carboxylic acid then conversion to dimethylamide.

Thus route: starting 4-methylanisole.

Step 1: Oxidize benzylic methyl to carboxylic acid (p-anisic acid). Use KMnO4 or CrO3/H2SO4, or Jones oxidation, or catalytic oxidation

